"基础交互类适合让 AI 把内容先放进输入框，或用回显工具确认拓展工具链路是否正常。" = "Basic interaction tools let AI place content into the input box first, or use echo to verify the local tool chain.";
"记忆操作类用于维护已经写入的长期记忆，包含分页查看、关键词筛选、内容编辑和归档恢复。" = "Memory tools maintain saved long-term memories, including paged browsing, keyword filtering, editing, archiving, and restoring.";
"文件操作类只能访问应用沙盒 Documents 目录，包含读取、搜索、写入、移动、复制、删除、差异查看和撤销最近修改。" = "File tools can only access the app sandbox Documents folder, including read, search, write, move, copy, delete, diff, and undo for the latest change.";
"数据库操作类面向聊天、配置与记忆数据库，查询工具只读，写入工具仍受审批策略和 SQL 限制保护。" = "Database tools target chat, configuration, and memory databases. Query tools are read-only, while write tools remain protected by approval policy and SQL restrictions.";
"反馈工单类用于把对话里的问题、复现步骤和建议整理为反馈记录。" = "Feedback ticket tools turn issues, reproduction steps, and suggestions from the conversation into feedback records.";
"先看当前会话能用什么，再按工具来源进入细分设置。" = "Check what the current session can use, then drill into settings by tool source.";
"工具中心新版说明正文" = "When to use\n• Quickly check which tools are truly available in the current session.\n• Adjust enablement and approval policies across different tool sources.\n\nHow to read this page\n• Configured enabled means the setting is turned on.\n• Available in current session means it can actually be sent to chat after global switches, approval policy, and session isolation are applied.\n• If the two numbers differ, it is usually because session conditions are limiting the tool, such as worldbook isolation.\n\nRecommended flow\n1. Start with the overview and check available counts for each tool type.\n2. Use Show Enabled Only to focus on active configuration.\n3. Enter the relevant tool source. App tools are grouped by basic interaction, memory, files, database, and feedback.\n4. Open a specific tool to adjust enablement, approval policy, or run mode.\n\nKey switches\n• Enable Memory controls whether memory-related built-in tools can participate in chat.\n• Expose tools to model controls whether an entire source is available to the model.\n• Approval policy decides whether calls ask first, pass automatically, or are denied.\n\nTroubleshooting\n• If a tool does not work, check Available in current session before Configured enabled.\n• When the session isolation notice is orange, memory, app tools, MCP, Agent Skills, and Shortcuts are blocked by the session policy.";
"拓展工具已按用途分组；进入分类后再查看具体工具、启用状态与审批策略。" = "App tools are grouped by purpose. Enter a category to review specific tools, enablement, and approval policy.";
"分类 %d 个" = "%d categories";
"按用途查看本地工具，先选类别，再调整具体工具。" = "Browse local tools by purpose. Choose a category first, then adjust specific tools.";
"拓展工具分类说明正文" = "Categories\n• Basic Interaction: let AI prepare drafts or verify the tool chain.\n• Memory Operations: view, edit, and archive long-term memories.\n• File Operations: access the app sandbox Documents folder, including read, write, move, delete, and undo.\n• Database Operations: inspect chat, configuration, and memory databases. Queries are read-only; writes remain protected by approval and SQL restrictions.\n• Feedback Tickets: turn issues or suggestions into tickets.\n\nRecommendations\n• Keep high-risk categories on Ask Every Time.\n• File and database tools require user confirmation by default. They are best for debugging and maintenance, not long-running silent automation.\n• If the current session uses worldbook isolation, these settings are kept but not actually exposed during chat.";
"工具分类" = "Tool Categories";
"工具 %d 个" = "%d tools";
"技能" = "Skills";
"当前还没有已导入的快捷指令工具。" = "No Shortcut tools have been imported yet.";
"把已安装技能通过 use_skill 暴露给模型。" = "Expose installed skills to the model through use_skill.";
"Agent Skills 工具说明正文" = "Agent Skills are useful for packaged workflows or specialized domain capabilities.\n\nThe global switch decides whether use_skill is exposed to the chat model. Individual switches decide whether each skill can be selected. If the current session uses worldbook isolation, skill settings are kept but not actually sent during chat.";
"把已导入的 Siri 快捷指令作为聊天工具使用。" = "Use imported Siri Shortcuts as chat tools.";
"快捷指令工具说明正文" = "Shortcut tools are useful for system automation, cross-app actions, or workflows you have already organized in Shortcuts.\n\nHere you can manage chat exposure, individual enablement, run mode, and tool descriptions. Calls still go through tool approval, which keeps higher-risk automation behind user confirmation.";
"先按用途选择分类，再进入具体工具。" = "Choose a category by purpose first, then open a specific tool.";
"系统自带能力集中在这里，按单项调整记忆、网页卡片、问答与时间工具。" = "System-provided capabilities live here. Adjust memory, web cards, Q&A, and time tools one by one.";
"内置工具说明正文" = "Built-in tools are provided directly by the app. They control core capabilities such as memory writing, active retrieval, web cards, structured Q&A, and system time.\n\nRecommendations\n• Check the Memory System switch first, then adjust memory writing and active retrieval.\n• Web cards, user questions, and system time are lightweight capabilities you can enable individually.\n• If the current session uses worldbook isolation, these settings are kept but not actually exposed during chat.";
"启用记忆系统后，记忆写入与主动检索工具才可能参与聊天。" = "After the Memory System is enabled, memory writing and active retrieval tools can participate in chat.";

